race.comment: STORM SEASON (6) narrowly on top. She resumed at Kembla Grange in a Class 1 over 1400m and got the job done, coming from midfield and booting clear to win well. Up slightly in trip will only suit better and there should be improvement to come having contested some strong 3yo races last time in work. HOLA AMIGOS (4) presents third up having improved nicely last start at Pakenham, sticking on well behind a smart horse. Peaks now from the good draw. ROGUERY (1) is off a let up having run a good race fresh at Seymour when running on well late. Don't mind him fresh again for the 1500m. DIVINE THOUGHTS (9) stuck on fairly well at Donald first up and will be fitter for it. She's better suited to the extra 150m here and can take catching around here. WELCOMETOTHESHOW (7) comes over from Adelaide in good form and can be hitting the line late.
